Package: gtable
Type: Package
Title: Arrange grobs in tables.
Version: 0.1.5
Author: Hadley Wickham <h.wickham@gmail.com>
Authors@R: c(person("Hadley", "Wickham",
    email = "h.wickham@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Baptiste", "Auguie",
    email = "baptiste.auguie@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut")),
    person("Paul", "Murrell",
    email = "paul@stat.auckland.ac.nz",
    role = c("aut")))
Description: Tools to make it easier to work with "tables" of grobs. A tabular
    layout is described by rectangular cells defining grid viewports, graphical
    objects (grobs) are positioned in relation to this layout. Convenience
    functions are provided to alter the layout (merge, bind, reshape, extract),
    add and remove grobs, and draw the resulting table.
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14),
    grid
Imports:
    plyr (>= 1.7.1)
Suggests:
    testthat
License: GPL-2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Enhances: gridExtra
Roxygen: list(wrap = FALSE)
URL: https://github.com/hadley/gtable
